body:
Currently, a crate can re-export item(s) from it's dependencies with inline documentation:
```rust
// hyperium/http

/// ```
/// use http::Request;
/// let req = Request::new();
/// ```
pub struct Request;
```
```rust
// hyperium/hyper

#[doc(inline)]
pub use http::{Response, Request};
```

However, documentation tests still display imports from the original crate, meaning if someone goes to the documentation for `hyper::Request`, they will see it being imported from a different crate:
```rust
// docs.rs/hyper/struct.Request.html

use http::Request;
let req = Request::new();
```

This is potentially confusing for users. This issue proposes renaming doctest imports on re-exported items:
```rust
// docs.rs/hyper/struct.Request.html

use hyper::Request;
let req = Request::new();
```

There may also be a way to disable this functionality:
```rust
#[doc(inline, rename = false)]
pub use http::{Response, Request};
```
